            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See letter and enclosure from T. H. Huxley, 23 December 1874. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref> had sent CD a copy of his letter to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3350.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">St George Jackson Mivart</ref> censuring him for his failure to apologise for an attack on an article by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1224.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">George Howard Darwin</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">For Mivart’s rejoinder, see <hi rend="italic">Quarterly Review</hi> 137 (1874): 588–9, and Appendix V.</note>
